            . I am an apprentice to Mr. Thomas Nicholls, a <rs id="t18320705-275-viclabel1444" type="occupation">pawnbroker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320705-275-victim2248 t18320705-275-viclabel1444"></join>, in <placeName id="t18320705-275-crimeloc1445">Gray's Inn-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320705-275-crimeloc1445" type="placeName" value="Gray's Inn-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320705-275-crimeloc1445" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320705-275-off1442 t18320705-275-crimeloc1445"></join>. On the 3rd of July the prisoners came to the shop; Thomas came to take out a pair of stockings - I let her have them; Lloyd had come and asked the price of a quilt the day before, and on this day they asked to look at it; Thomas then took the stockings, and went away, telling Lloyd to wait till she came back - she came; they staid some time, and then went away: I then missed the quilt - I had known them before; I found where they lived, and went with an officer to their lodgings - I found Thomas in the room, and this quilt on the bed; Lloyd was in the room over it - I had not seen either of them take the quilt; this is it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320705-275-person2250">
                  RICHARD 
                  BAYLIS
               <interp inst="t18320705-275-person2250" type="surname" value="BAYLIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320705-275-person2250" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320705-275-person2250" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            (Police-constable G 67). I went and asked Lloyd what she had done with the quilt - she said she knew nothing of it; that it was in the room below: I went and found it in the room where Thomas was.</p>
               <p>Thomas' Defence. I went to get the stockings, and picked up this quilt; I took it home, and it laid there an hour or better - he then came and said it was his master's; I said I did not know, he could have it if he pleased; he said No, he would not, he would send for an officer.</p>
               <p>Lloyd put in a written Defence, denying that she was aware of the theft.</p>
               <p>THOMAS - <rs id="t18320705-275-verdict1446" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320705-275-verdict1446" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 22.</p>
